1. Get Setup

1.1. Clear everything $ set width

options(width=80) #Set width
rm(list=ls())     #Remove everything from environment
cat("\014")       #Clear Console

1.2. Loading necessary packages

pacman::p_load(
        knitr,
        codebook,  #package for creating codebooks in Rmarkdown
        ggplot2,   #data visualizations
        here,       #file locator
        expss,      #variable and value labels
        tidyverse
)

1.3. Knitr preferences

knitr::opts_chunk$set(
  warning = TRUE, # show warnings during codebook generation
  message = TRUE, # show messages during codebook generation
  error = TRUE, # do not interrupt codebook generation in case of errors,
                # usually better for debugging
  echo = TRUE  # show R code
)
ggplot2::theme_set(ggplot2::theme_bw())

2. Load the data

source(here::here("modules", "02_data_management", "module_4_labels", 
                  "data_label_practice.R"))
data_codebook <- some_data
data_codebook <- data_codebook
codebook(data_codebook)
